    {
      "id": "ec5e9ffb71b7a386fd04fad1fa780d8995e9630d",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 192,
        "name": "Brian Behlendorf",
        "email": "behlendorf1@llnl.gov",
        "inactive": true
      },
      "date": "2012-05-08 16:01:29.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 2:\n\nWe just observed this issue as well without the proposed patch applied.  We've not picked up the fix although I suspect it won't actually address the root cause of the issue.\n\nWhen we saw this problem we still had 40GB (of 192GB of memory) free on the system so it was not yet over committed.  I suspect the issue relates more to having all these threads get serialized attempting to concurrently vmalloc() some address space.  It's probably worth considering moving these allocations to slabs if possible, I noticed many of the allocation sizes are fairly small.\n\nAnyway, we'll report back if we observe the issue with the patch now applied.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 2
    }
